Package: statlingua
Type: Package
Title: Explain Statistical Output with Large Language Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(c("Brandon", "M."), family = "Greenwell", 
    email = "greenwell.brandon@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"), 
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8120-0084"))
Description: An R package leveraging large language models (LLMs) to help convert complex statistical output into straightforward, understandable, and context-aware natural language descriptions. By feeding your statistical models and outcomes into LLMs, you can effortlessly produce human-readable interpretations of coefficients, p-values, measures of model fit, and other key metrics, thereby democratizing statistical understanding for individuals with varying levels of technical expertise.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
License: GPL (>= 3)
URL: https://github.com/bgreenwell/statlingua, https://bgreenwell.github.io/statlingua/
